definitions.definition: Any of various common types of small insects or other animals which cause harm and annoyance .
examples: The area was crawling with all sorts of vermin : fleas, lice, mice, and rats to name a few. Thus, we felt as if vermin were crawling over us.

definitions.definition: An animal that preys on game , such as a fox or a weasel.
An obnoxious or mean and offensive person.
examples: Bring these vermin to the Palace of Justice.

main_definition: Any of various common types of small insects or other animals which cause harm and annoyance . [from c. 1300]
secondary_definitions: An animal that preys on game , such as a fox or a weasel.
An obnoxious or mean and offensive person. [from 1560s]
